.TH "atmel_i2c_checksum" 9 "atmel_i2c_checksum" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
atmel_i2c_checksum \- Generate 16-bit CRC as required by ATMEL ECC. CRC16 verification of the count, opcode, param1, param2 and data bytes. The checksum is saved in little-endian format in the least significant two bytes of the command. CRC polynomial is 0x8005 and the initial register value should be zero.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" atmel_i2c_checksum
.BI "(struct atmel_i2c_cmd *cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cmd" 12
structure used for communicating with the device.
